Beets with Orange and Walnuts
  --America's Test Kitchen

1 1/2 lb beets, trimmed and halved horizontally
1 1/4 c water
salt and pepper
3 tbsp white vinegar
1 tbsp packed light brown sugar
1 shallot, sliced thin
1 tsp grated orange zest
1/2 c walnuts, toasted and chopped
2 tbsp chopped fresh parsley
1 tsp chopped fresh thyme

Place beets cut side down in single layer in 11" traight sided saute pan or dutch oven. Add water and 1/4 tsp salt; bring to simmer over high heat. Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer until beets are tender and tip of paring knife inserted into beets meets no resistance, 45-50 min. Transfer beets to cutting board, increase heat to medium high and reduce cooking liquid, stirring ocasionally, until pan is almost dry, 5-6 min. Add vinegar and sugar; return to boil; and cook, stirring occasionally, until spatula leaves wide trail when dragged through glaze, 1-2 min. Remove pan from heat. When beets are cool enough to handle, rub off skins with paper towl or dish towel and cut into 1/2" wedges. Add beets, shallot, orange zest, 1/2 tsp salt, and 1/4 tsp pepper to glaze and toss to coat. Transfer to serving dish; sprinkle with walnuts, parsley, and thyme; serve.

Notes: If serving room temp, wait to sprinkle walnuts, etc until right before serving.
